# id: WebHttpHandlerBuilder -> public static WebHttpHandlerBuilder applicationContext(ApplicationContext context)
commentText:
Factory method to create a new builder instance by detecting beans in an_{@link ApplicationContext}. The following are detected:_
    _
  • {@link WebHandler} [1] -- looked up by the name_{@link #WEB_HANDLER_BEAN_NAME}._
  • {@link WebFilter} [0..N] -- detected by type and ordered,_see {@link AnnotationAwareOrderComparator}._
  • {@link WebExceptionHandler} [0..N] -- detected by type and_ordered._
  • {@link WebSessionManager} [0..1] -- looked up by the name_{@link #WEB_SESSION_MANAGER_BEAN_NAME}._
_@param context the application context to use for the lookup_@return the prepared builder
codeText: public static WebHttpHandlerBuilder applicationContext(ApplicationContext context) {__		__		WebHttpHandlerBuilder builder = new WebHttpHandlerBuilder(_				context.getBean(WEB_HANDLER_BEAN_NAME, WebHandler.class))___		__		Collection<WebFilter> filters = BeanFactoryUtils.beansOfTypeIncludingAncestors(_				context, WebFilter.class, true, false).values()___		WebFilter[] sortedFilters = filters.toArray(new WebFilter[filters.size()])__		AnnotationAwareOrderComparator.sort(sortedFilters)__		builder.filters(sortedFilters)___		__		Collection<WebExceptionHandler> handlers = BeanFactoryUtils.beansOfTypeIncludingAncestors(_				context, WebExceptionHandler.class, true, false).values()___		WebExceptionHandler[] sortedHandlers = handlers.toArray(new WebExceptionHandler[handlers.size()])__		AnnotationAwareOrderComparator.sort(sortedHandlers)__		builder.exceptionHandlers(sortedHandlers)___		__		try {_			builder.sessionManager(_					context.getBean(WEB_SESSION_MANAGER_BEAN_NAME, WebSessionManager.class))__		}_		catch (NoSuchBeanDefinitionException ex) {_			_		}__		return builder__	}
